               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel, Homiliary for the feasts of St Michael (fols.
                     1ra-46rb) 
 I-1) Homily by Timothy (Dumatewos), Patriarch of Alexandria for
                     the 12th of Ḫǝdār (fols. 1ra-7ra); miracle (fols. 7ra-8va); commemorative
                     notice (fols. 8va-9ra); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 9ra) 
 I-2) Homily by an anonymous
                     author for Tāḫśāś (fols. 9rb-11vb, 40ra-41vb); miracle (fols. 12ra-rb, 13ra-vb,
                     41vb); commemorative notice (fol. 12rb-vb); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 12vb) 
 I-3)
                     Homily [by Epiphanius, Metropolitan of Cyprus] for Ṭǝrr (fols. 12vb, 14ra-15vb,
                     17ra-18vb, 19ra, 32ra-35vb); miracle (fols. 16ra-rb,19ra-vb); commemorative
                     notice (fol. 16rb-va); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 16va-vb) 
 I-4) Homily by "one of
                     the ancient saints, the Orthodox" [anonymous author] for the 12th of Yakkātit
                     (fols. 16vb, 20ra-26rb); miracle (fols. 26rb-27rb); commemorative notice (fol.
                     27rb-va); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 27va-vb) 
 I-5) Homily by Yoḥannǝs, Metropolitan
                     of ʾAksum for Sane (fols. 27vb, 28ra-31vb, 36ra-37vb, 38ra); miracle (fol.
                     38ra-vb); commemorative notice (fols. 38vb-39vb, 42ra); ʾarke-hymn (fol. 42ra)
                     
 I-6) Homily by the 24 Heavenly Priests [anonymous author] [for Naḥāse]
                     (fols. 42ra-45rb); miracle (fols. 45rb-46ra); commemorative notice (fol. 46rb);
                     ʾarke-hymn (fol. 46rb) 
 II) Malkǝʾa Mikāʾel “Image of Michael” (fols.
                     47va-52ra) 
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>
